==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Occident
<hw>Oc"ci*dent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>occidens</ets>, <ets>occidentis</ets>, fr. <ets>occidents</ets>, p.
pr. of <ets>occidere</ets> to fall or go down. See
<er>Occasion</er>.]</ety> <def>The part of the horizon where the sun
last appears in the evening; that part of the earth towards the sunset;
the west; -- opposed to <ant>orient</ant>. Specifically, in former
times, Europe as opposed to Asia; now, also, the Western
hemisphere.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I may wander from east to <qex>occident</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Occidental</ent>⟦br⟧
